description:
Retrieves last item of the array.

Example:
1. [1,2]@0 received via `array`
2. 2@0 sent via `item`

More:
https://github.com/Cranq-io/cranq-tutorials/tree/main/reference/3_querying_data/3_1_getters#getting-the-first--last-array-elements

e4936450-3660-45ac-8cb5-7699ba69ba66.description:
Recieves array to retrieve last item from.

Example:
[1,2]
e4936450-3660-45ac-8cb5-7699ba69ba66.name: array

e6cf79e7-8084-402e-a28c-82b50b07e0ec.description:
Sends last item of the array.

Example:
2
e6cf79e7-8084-402e-a28c-82b50b07e0ec.name: item

name: data/array/Last item getter
